            <h2>What septic tank cleaning actually solves</h2>
            <p>A septic tank works by separating solids from liquids and slowly digesting the solids over time. When solids build up too long, they overflow into the leach field and clog it. Replacing a leach field is expensive; a regular tank cleaning is not.</p><p>Honest Drain coordinates the tank cleaning, handles drain-side cleaning of the line feeding the tank, and explains realistic intervals for the household based on tank size and use.</p>
